# 6. 思い出

Mafuyu: ...
Mizuki: There are more people who will accept me for who I am than I realized.
Mizuki: Now, I have a feeling that there'll be more people that'll say, “Thanks for telling me,” and, “No matter what, I'm on your side,” after breaking some big news to them...
Mizuki: That's how I feel now...
Mafuyu: (Would he..?)
Mafuyu: (Would he say that...?)
Mafuyu: But...
Mafuyu: ...
???: <Mafuyu...>
Mafuyu: Huh...?
Mafuyu: Rin...
Rin: <You still don't look so good, Mafuyu...>
Mafuyu: ...
Rin: <Were you thinking about that dream you saw last night...?>
Mafuyu: Yes...
Rin: <I see...>
Rin: <If you're that scared, then you don't have to tell him...>
Mafuyu: But...
Rin: <...>
Mafuyu: My dad's been coming over to see me every week... And I've done nothing in return...
Mafuyu: Also...
Mafuyu: I made him make that face...
Mafuyu: So...
Mafuyu: I want to tell him about what happened that night...
Mafuyu: I want to... But...
Rin: <...>
Rin: <Actually, Mafuyu...>
Rin: <What is your dad like?>
Mafuyu: Huh...?
Mafuyu: Ordinary...
Mafuyu: Work keeps him very busy, so he's hardly ever at home.
Rin: <That's not what I'm asking...>
Mafuyu: Huh...?
Rin: <What does he mean to you, Mafuyu?>
Mafuyu: To me...?
Mafuyu: I don't know... Even when I was little, he was rarely at home because he was so busy.
Mafuyu: But...
Mafuyu: My mom always said, “Your father is working very hard for both of us,” and, “You need to do your best to be a good girl for your father's sake.”
Mafuyu: Also...
Mafuyu's Mother: Okay, the sides are ready. All that's left is for us to put in the rice balls, and it'll be complete.
Little Mafuyu: Wow...!
Little Mafuyu: This lunch looks really yummy...!
Little Mafuyu: Hehe. Thank you, Mommy!
Little Mafuyu: But I still wish Daddy could come to sports day...
Mafuyu's Mother: There isn't much we can do since work is keeping him very busy. But I promise to take as many pictures I can of you.
Mafuyu's Mother: And then, I'll show them to your father.
Little Mafuyu: Okay...! I'm gonna run as fast as I can!
Mafuyu's Mother: Happy birthday, Mafuyu!
Mafuyu's Mother: Let me see you blow out all the candles.
Little Mafuyu: Okay!
Little Mafuyu: *Blow*
Mafuyu's Mother: Hehe. You did it!
Mafuyu's Mother: Alright, this is from me... And here's the present your father got you.
Little Mafuyu: Oh, thank you!
Little Mafuyu: Is Daddy busy with work again today?
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes, he was hoping to be back in time for your birthday party, but things are apparently taking longer than he was expecting...
Little Mafuyu: Okay...
Little Mafuyu: I still wish he were here, but I guess there isn't anything we can do.
Little Mafuyu: Because he's working really hard for us, right?
Mafuyu's Mother: Hehe. Yes, that's right. He said he should be able to come home early tomorrow, so you should thank him then.
Little Mafuyu: Okay!
Junior High School Mafuyu: (The entrance ceremony for high schoolers is tomorrow...)
Junior High School Mafuyu: (But not much is really changing since I'll still be attending the same academy.)
Junior High School Mafuyu: Oh...
Junior High School Mafuyu: Welcome back, Dad. You're home early today...
Mafuyu's Father: Yes, things worked out today, but I'll be leaving tomorrow for another business trip.
Mafuyu's Father: So, Mafuyu, why don't we take this opportunity to go out for some sushi and...
Mafuyu's Father: It's from work. But why at this time...?
Mafuyu's Father: Hello? Is something the matter?
Mafuyu's Father: Oh, that's not good... Okay, I'll be right over.
Mafuyu's Father: Sorry, Mafuyu. Looks like sushi will have to wait until after my trip.
Junior High School Mafuyu: Sure, that's fine.
Junior High School Mafuyu: Good luck with work, Dad.
Mafuyu: That's how things always were...
Rin: <...>
Rin: <Is that really it?>
Mafuyu: Huh...?
Rin: <I mean, all you basically told me was that your dad was never home.>
Rin: <Don't you have any other memories of him?>
Mafuyu: Other memories...?
Mafuyu: What else is there...?
Rin: <...!!!>
Rin: <Wh-What was that sound just now...?>
Mafuyu: Just now?
Mafuyu: Oh, that was thunder.
Rin: <Thunder...?>
Rin: <...!!!>
Mafuyu: Are you okay?
Rin: <I-I'm fine... But...>
Rin: <M-Mafuyu, aren't you scared...?>
Mafuyu: I'm...
Mafuyu: ...? A message...?
Mafuyu: From who?
Mafuyu's Father's Message: <Are you okay? This thunderstorm's massive.>
Mafuyu: Oh...
Rin: <Mafuyu?>
Mafuyu: There was this one time...
